{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"01473e37-a520-4f53-9e2d-d6cba8c34773","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest bridge adapter by default.**\n\nIn 3.x, the SDK still shipped the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge` so tools like `vstest.console.exe` could discover tests. In 4.x, the SDK targets **Microsoft.Testing.Platform exclusively** — the VSTest adapter is no longer included, which is why `vstest.console` sees zero tests.\n\n### You have two options\n\n**Option A – Re-enable the VSTest bridge** (quick CI fix):\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Option B – Migrate CI away from `vstest.console`** (recommended long-term):\n\nReplace your `vstest.console` invocation with either:\n\n- **`dotnet test`** (SDK ≥ 9.0.200 uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively), or\n- **Run the test executable directly**: `dotnet build && ./bin/Debug/net8.0/TestProject.exe`\n\nWould you like me to update your `TestProject.csproj` with one of these approaches?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"147218cd-de55-45fd-a8e0-b9ae1bd3eec6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a well-known breaking change in MSTest.Sdk. Let me explain what happened.\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 3.x, the SDK used Microsoft.Testing.Platform (the new test platform) by default. However, it still included the VSTest bridge/adapter so that `vstest.console` and `dotnet test` (which uses VSTest under the hood) could still discover and run tests.\n\nIn MSTest.Sdk 4.x, the VSTest bridge adapter is no longer included by default. The SDK now exclusively targets Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This means:\n\n1. `vstest.console.exe` can no longer discover or run the tests\n\n\n2. `dotnet test` works with .NET SDK 9.0.200+ since it switched to using Microsoft.Testing.Platform directly\n\nTo fix this, you can either re-enable the VSTest bridge through a project property, or update your CI pipeline to use `dotnet test` with a modern .NET SDK or run the test executable directly.","outputTokens":645,"requestId":"7032:18DB54:4A9718:5743A0:69F2C3F3"},"id":"9d5ebd3c-1e16-4163-bc42-88ceb115929f","timestamp":"2026-04-30T02:52:47.986Z","parentId":"6b020500-fa99-409d-b6fd-f20528710a0c"}
